  'You are performing a private consulting locational analysis at 412 Riverside Drive, Greer, SC 29651. The subject is 3BR/2BA · 1,840 SF · 2004-built SFR · Riverside Commons. Private consulting assignment. Client is a buy-and-hold investor evaluating this property for long-term single-family rental. The Greer/Duncan submarket has an active international worker rental segment driven by BMW Manufacturing and its supplier ecosystem. The investor wants to understand whether this location supports that demand base and what locational factors affect long-term hold value. Section 5 — Locational Influence — requires you to identify which locational factors are present at the subject, classify each as Positive, Negative, Neutral, or Market-Dependent based on the location profile evidence and the investor lens, and write a brief market-supported rationale for each classification. Investor consulting analysis differs from owner-occupant appraisal: rental demand drivers, trajectory signals, and exit-strategy considerations may shift the analytical weight or even the classification of a factor relative to a standard purchase appraisal. Distractor factors that are not present must be left unchecked, and each rationale must cite specific evidence and connect the factor to the investor''s stated strategy.'
