  'You are performing a private consulting locational analysis at 1234 Cleveland Street, Greenville, SC 29601. The subject is 3BR/1.5BA · 1,420 SF · 1952-built SFR (updated 2019) · Cleveland Park Fringe. Private consulting assignment. Client is a value-add investor evaluating this property for long-term rental hold. The investor is specifically interested in neighborhood trajectory — whether observable market signals indicate an improving or declining trend — as a primary factor in the hold-value decision. Section 5 — Locational Influence — requires you to identify which locational factors are present at the subject, classify each as Positive, Negative, Neutral, or Market-Dependent based on the location profile evidence and the investor lens, and write a brief market-supported rationale for each classification. Investor consulting analysis differs from owner-occupant appraisal: rental demand drivers, trajectory signals, and exit-strategy considerations may shift the analytical weight or even the classification of a factor relative to a standard purchase appraisal. Distractor factors that are not present must be left unchecked, and each rationale must cite specific evidence and connect the factor to the investor''s stated strategy.'
