  'You are performing a private consulting locational analysis at 2847 Augusta Road, Greenville, SC 29605. The subject is 4BR/2.5BA · 2,060 SF · 1978-built SFR (renovated 2021) · Augusta Road / Overbrook. Private consulting assignment. Client is an institutional investor evaluating this property as part of a portfolio acquisition. The investor requires a comprehensive locational analysis that explicitly distinguishes factors affecting immediate rental marketability from factors affecting long-term hold value and exit strategy — and that identifies any factors whose analytical classification would differ between an owner-occupant appraisal and this investor consulting assignment. Section 5 — Locational Influence — requires you to identify which locational factors are present at the subject, classify each as Positive, Negative, Neutral, or Market-Dependent based on the location profile evidence and the investor lens, and write a brief market-supported rationale for each classification. Investor consulting analysis differs from owner-occupant appraisal: rental demand drivers, trajectory signals, and exit-strategy considerations may shift the analytical weight or even the classification of a factor relative to a standard purchase appraisal. Distractor factors that are not present must be left unchecked, and each rationale must cite specific evidence and connect the factor to the investor''s stated strategy.'
FROM scenario_categories WHERE code = 'M2-S5-C4';

